==Irish==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|[krak&#690;]}}

===Etymology===
16th Century English [[crack]].
Many words in current usage throughout Ireland are from previous centuries.  While in England some of these older words have long since passed out of usage, in much of Ireland they are still in use.  Crack is one of these words.  The word was, at some point, adopted into [[Irish Gaelic]], and is spelled 'craic'.

